Ah, sorry. This is the configuration for Windows.

We need to enable Gandiva explicitly:

{noformat}
mvn generate-resources -Pgenerate-libs-jni-macos-linux -DARROW_GANDIVA=ON -DARROW_JAVA_JNI_ENABLE_GANDIVA=ON -N
{noformat}

For C data, we also need {{-DARROW_JAVA_JNI_ENABLE_C=ON}} and {{-Darrow.c.jni.dist.dir}}:

{noformat}
mvn generate-resources -Pgenerate-libs-jni-macos-linux -DARROW_GANDIVA=ON -DARROW_JAVA_JNI_ENABLE_GANDIVA=ON -DARROW_JAVA_JNI_ENABLE_C=ON -N
mvn -Darrow.cpp.build.dir=$PWD/../java-dist/lib/ -Darrow.c.jni.dist.dir=$PWD/../java-dist/lib/ -Parrow-jni clean install
{noformat}

This works @kou! I'll open a PR for the docs.
The only thing I had to do extra was install protobuf for aarch_64 as suggested by the error I pasted above:
{code:bash}
mvn install:install-file -DgroupId=com.google.protobuf -DartifactId=protoc -Dversion=3.20.3 -Dclassifier=osx-aarch_64 -Dpackaging=exe -Dfile=/path/to/file
{code}
I wonder if that can be automated somehow.
